ANTHRAX, BOVINE - MONGOLIA (KHOVSGOL): REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 25 Jan 2009
Source: hnwchina.com [Trans. by submitter, edited]
<http://www.hnwchina.com/news/gj/141011.html>


China is reporting anthrax in one cow in Khovsgol Province, Mongolia.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Dan Silver

[This brief report is confirmed by www.sanxia.net.cn at
<http://news.sanxia.net.cn/html/20090125/188996.html>.

At the time we received this report we asked for confirmation and
details from Ulaan Bataar but to date have not received a reply. Any
information clarifying how this winter outbreak of anthrax occurred
would be appreciated. In my experience such winter outbreaks are
usually related to contaminated stored forage or feed. ProMED-mail
regrets the delay in posting. - Mod.MHJ
